      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">Title III of the E-Government Act, titled the Federal Information
                Security Management Act (FISMA) of 2002, tasked NIST to develop (1) standards to be
                used by all Federal agencies to categorize information and information systems
                collected or maintained by or on behalf of each agency based on the objectives of
                providing appropriate levels of information security according to a range of risk
                levels; and (2) guidelines recommending the types of information and information
                systems to be included in each such category. Special Publication 800-60 was issued
                in response to the second of these tasks. The revision to Volume I contains the
                basic guidelines for mapping types of information and information systems to
                security categories. The appendices contained in Volume I include security
                categorization recommendations and rationale for mission-based and management and
                support information types.</abstract>
